To run the demo on your Windows machine, you will need to follow the steps provided below:

 

Install Python 3.x on your Windows machine if you don't already have it installed. You can download it from the official website: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/.

 

Install pip, the Python package installer, using the following command in the command prompt: python -m ensurepip --default-pip

 

*Clone the demo repository from Github using the following command in the command prompt: git clone https://github.com/your-repo-url.git

 

Navigate to the project directory and install the required dependencies using the following command: pip install -r requirements.txt

 

Run the Django development server using the following command: python manage.py runserver

 

Open a Ib browser and navigate to http://localhost:8000/ to see the demo in action.

 

